      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "HASH VAULT - skip the API call when you've already generated this exact prompt.\n\nFLOW\nOne prompt feeds BOTH Hash Vault (which computes a SHA-256 of it) AND Gemini. Hash Vault looks in output/hash_vault/ for a .pt file matching that hash. If found -> cache hit, is_cached=1, cached_data contains the image. If not -> cache miss, is_cached=0.\n\nLazy API Switch reads is_cached and demands ONLY ONE branch:\n  hit  -> reads cached_data. The Gemini -> Hash Vault Save branch is never executed. $0.00 billed.\n  miss -> demands api_data, which forces Gemini to run, then Hash Vault Save writes the result to disk so the next run with the same prompt is a hit.\n\nCHANGE THE PROMPT -> new hash -> cache miss -> Gemini runs. Re-run with the same prompt -> cache hit -> no API call, no cost.\n\nREQUIRES\nComfyUI-API-Optimizer (Hash Vault nodes), ComfyUI-Gemini-Direct (Gemini node), ComfyUI-KJNodes (StringConstantMultiline). Any STRING primitive works in place of KJNodes' node - the point is that a single string source drives both the hash and the API input."
      ]
    },
